Cancer Talk Blog

Breast Cancer in Men: Owen’s Story

   Friday, October 4, 2019 - 5:09pm
   [owen_male_breast_cancer_2019.jpg?itok=xzgPZcB0]

   Not everyone realizes men can get breast cancer, though not nearly as
   often as women. Older men get it more than younger men, but breast
   cancer can occur at any age. And in anyone.

Raising Awareness for Breast Reconstruction

   Wednesday, October 2, 2019 - 4:30pm
   [adobestock_138800993.jpg?itok=6oIMkerH]

   As a surgeon in the Department of Head and Neck Surgery/Plastic and
   Reconstructive Surgery at Roswell Park Comprehensive Cancer Center, I
   work very closely with breast cancer patients to help educate them on
   their options and the benefits of breast reconstruction after their
   cancer treatment. Here are some of the most common questions that I'm
   asked when meeting with a patient for the first time.

A Cure for Cancer: What's Taking So Long?

   Monday, September 30, 2019 - 1:36pm
   [nci-vol-10578-150.jpg?itok=kBblpzQI]
   More than a century ago, scientists predicted that a cure for cancer
   was just five years away. So what happened? Here's what we know now
   that we didn't know then.
   More Blog Entries

Spotlight

The Roswell Difference

   [roswell_difference.png]

   Roswell Park was the first center in the world to focus exclusively on
   cancer. Roswell Park is determined to eliminate cancer's grip on
   humanity, one patient at a time.

   Learn More


Know Your Risk

   [tesse_flores_and_mary_reid_-_cancer_screening_january_24_2018_7.jpg]

   Screening tests detect cancer’s hidden warning signs long before
   symptoms appear and when the disease is most treatable. Understand your
   screening needs and complete the cancer screening and prevention
   questionnaire to manage your cancer risk.

   Learn More

2019-20 Best Hospitals

   [us-news-14.png]

   Roswell Park is ranked among the top cancer hospitals in the nation in
   U.S. News & World Report's 2019-20 Best Hospitals.

   Learn More

